<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-219] Permanent deactivating an OST does survive after reboot</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-219</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As described in &lt;a href=&quot;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;14.8.3.  Removing an OST from the File System&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there is not expected to be a replacement for this OST in the near future, permanently deactivate the OST on all clients and the MDS:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;mgs&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lctl conf_param ost_name.osc.active=0&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;However, after reboot, the OST would become active &quot;UP&quot; again while it should be always inactive &quot;IN&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre 2.3/IEEL 1.0</environment>
        <key id="22862">LUDOC-219</key>
